too. Okay. Let me go back over. Vikram asks, you recommended caching your pins to speed up apps

01:12:20.879 --> 01:12:25.680
using data that doesn't change often. Any tips for more dynamic data?

01:12:29.439 --> 01:12:35.200
So dynamic data. Well, maybe one tip I can give you, if you're talking about dynamic data,

01:12:35.279 --> 01:12:42.160
often bring it from a database. Especially since we're a startup company, we basically

01:12:43.200 --> 01:12:48.959
just started somewhere. We had a database, which was fine. As soon as we started looking into

01:12:48.959 --> 01:12:54.160
optimizing the database as well, changing the number of cores, changing the availability there,

01:12:54.720 --> 01:13:00.399
massive gains. So if you can pull data from a database and your database is fast enough and

01:13:01.200 --> 01:13:07.279
organized well, because organization matters, where do you put your indexes? How are you going

01:13:07.279 --> 01:13:14.160
to make sure that data can easily be retrieved? Then I would definitely look into that.

01:13:15.919 --> 01:13:20.720
It's just whenever you're developing an app and you need to put in data, you always have to

01:13:20.720 --> 01:13:28.319
ask yourself, do I really need everything of this data? If not, can I make it smaller?

01:13:28.399 --> 01:13:33.120
And where does this data come from? And can I make wherever it came from faster? Yes or no?

